  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 in a Risk-Off Medium regime, driven by hawkish Fed signals and Eurozone deterioration, but H4 CSM has USD collapsing to 0 while CHF surges to 100 and NZD rockets to 82 \u2014 this USD fade versus H4 CSM is the dominant short-term signal. GBPJPY is the cleanest expression with D1+H4 both Buy and GBPUSD correlation at 0.89 amplifying the move; USDCHF H4 Buy at +4 conflicts with CHF H4 CSM dominance at 100, meaning USDCHF longs carry real reversal risk.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: GBPJPY CMP 56 with H4 momentum 76 accelerating strongly above D1\nFading: EURUSD CMP 40 with D1 momentum 37 and falling, AUDUSD CMP 46 with D1 44 declining\n\nWATCH\nEurozone data release hits EURUSD; D1 and H4 both Sell with EUR D1 CSM at 1 confirms continuation lower toward recent lows\nBoJ commentary crosses wires affecting USDJPY; D1 Buy but H4 fading to Neutral signals a stall and potential rejection at current levels\nUS yields extend their drop in USDJPY; the 10Y already down 2% and further decline breaks the D1 Buy thesis entirely",
